r=31\n |EpisodeNumber2=5\n |Title=Turtles in Space, Part 5 - Triceraton Wars\n |DirectedBy=Chuck Patton\n |WrittenBy=Michael Ryan\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2003|12|6}}\n |ProdCode=S02E05\n |ShortSummary=The turtles are faced with their biggest challenge yet, getting home!\n\n* Villains: The Federation and the Triceratons\n* Based on Microseries, Fugitoid Issue #1, \"The Fugitoid\u2019s Origin\" and Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles, Volume One Issue #5, \"Teaming Up with Fugitoid\",Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles, Volume One Issue #5, \"Teaming Up with Fugitoid\" and Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles, Volume One Issue #6, \"The Triceraton Homeworld\".\n\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=32\n |EpisodeNumber2=6\n |Title=Secret Origins, Part 1\n |DirectedBy=Chuck Patton\n |WrittenBy=Eric Luke\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2004|1|17}}\n |ProdCode=S02E06\n |ShortSummary=The Turtles are teleported back to Earth with Professor Honeycutt by the Utroms and they're reunited with Master Splinter. The Utroms take the Turtles and Splinter to the oracle pod chamber, a [[virtual reality]] simulation that chronicles historical events. Inside the chamber, the Turtles are transported to [[Shogun#Seii Taishogun of Feudal Period Japan (1185 - 1868)|feudal era Japan]] where they learn of the Utroms crash-landing on Earth. It is here, they encounter an early incarnation of the [[Foot Clan]] led by a look-alike of [[The Shredder]].<ref>[http://www.ninjaturtles.com/cartoon/2003/synopses/32.html Secret Origins, Part 1] Ninja Turtles Official Website. February 19, 2008</ref>\n\n* Villain: Feudal Shredder\n* Based on Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles, Volume One Issue #7, \"All is Revealed\".\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=33\n |EpisodeNumber2=7\n |Title=Secret Origins, Part 2\n |DirectedBy=Chuck Patton\n |WrittenBy=Michael Ryan\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2004|1|24}}\n |ProdCode=S02E07\n |ShortSummary=After [[Baxter Stockman]] infiltrates the TCRI building and sabotages the oracle pod cha