e form]] \u2013 a centuries-old criminal Utrom. However, despite his maliciousness, the Turtles and their sensei come to the realization that the Shredder also played an instrumental role in their own origins.\n\n* Villain: The Shredder\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=36\n |EpisodeNumber2=10\n |Title=The Ultimate Ninja\n |DirectedBy=Chuck Patton\n |WrittenBy=Michael Ryan\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2004|2|7}}\n |ProdCode=S02E10\n |ShortSummary=The Turtles, Splinter, [[Casey Jones|Casey]] and [[April O'Neil|April]] relax in the lair for a movie night. However, during an ice cream run, [[Leonardo (TMNT)|Leonardo]] is challenged to a [[gyoji]]-refereed duel by a headstrong young ninja from another dimension. The challenge comes in a tradition unfamiliar to Leonardo, but worrisome familiar to Master Splinter.<ref>[http://www.ninjaturtles.com/cartoon/2003/synopses/35.html The Ultimate Ninja] Ninja Turtles Official Website. February 19, 2008</ref>\n*Villain: The Ultimate Ninja\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=37\n |EpisodeNumber2=11\n |Title=The Return of Nano\n |DirectedBy=Chuck Patton\n |WrittenBy=Eric Luke\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2004|2|21}}\n |ProdCode=S02E11\n |ShortSummary=Nano, the [[nanorobotics|nanorobot]] who met his supposed [[Nano (TMNT 2003 Episode)|demise]] in the junyard, reawakens and reassembles. With a newfound motivation to create a [[nuclear family|family]], Nano breaks his \"father,\" [[Harry Parker (TMNT)|Harry Parker]], out of [[Rikers Island]] prison and kidnaps his \"mother\", [[Dr. Richards]], from her laboratory. When his \"family\" doesn't turn out as he hoped, Nano begins to wreak havoc on [[Coney Island]], where April and Casey happen to be on a \"not-a-[[courtship|date]].\"\n\n* Villain: Nano\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=38\n |EpisodeNumber2=12\n |Title=What a Croc!\n |DirectedBy=Chuck Patton\n |WrittenBy=[[Ben Townsend]]\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2004|2|28}}\n |ProdCode=S02E12\n |ShortSummary=Michelangelo 