 3\n |DirectedBy=Chuck Patton\n |WrittenBy=Marty Isenberg\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2004|1|31}}\n |ProdCode=S02E08\n |ShortSummary=The Turtles and [[Master Splinter|Splinter]] activate the internal fail safe of the oracle pod chamber only to find the TCRI building besieged by multiple enemies. The [[United States National Guard|National Guard]] stands outside the building trying to get in while the Shredder leads an attack with the Foot at the heart of the Utrom's base. The Turtles and Splinter help the Utroms evacuate and escape the Shredder's wrath, and they soon learn of the Shredder's true form.\n\n* Villains: The Foot Clan\n* Based on Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles, Volume One Issue #7, \"All is Revealed\".<ref>[http://www.ninjaturtles.com/cartoon/2003/synopses/34.html Secret Origins, Part 3] Ninja Turtles Official Website. February 19, 2008</ref>\n\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=35\n |EpisodeNumber2=9\n |Title=Reflections\n |DirectedBy=Chuck Patton\n |WrittenBy=[[Roland Gonzalez]]\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2004|2|14}}\n |ProdCode=S02E09\n |ShortSummary=The gang return to the farmhouse in [[Northampton, Massachusetts|Northampton]] to rest and recuperate. Taking a [[clip show|retrospective]] look at the recent events, they discuss their encounters with the Shredder as well as the discovery of his [[Secret Origins (TMNT 2003 Episode)|true form]] \u2013 a centuries-old criminal Utrom. However, despite his maliciousness, the Turtles and their sensei come to the realization that the Shredder also played an instrumental role in their own origins.\n\n* Villain: The Shredder\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=36\n |EpisodeNumber2=10\n |Title=The Ultimate Ninja\n |DirectedBy=Chuck Patton\n |WrittenBy=Michael Ryan\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2004|2|7}}\n |ProdCode=S02E10\n |ShortSummary=The Turtles, Splinter, [[Casey Jones|Casey]] and [[April O'Neil|April]] relax in the lair for a movie night. However, during an ice cream run, [[Leonardo (TMNT)|Leonardo]] is challenged to a [[gyoji]]-refereed duel by a headstrong young ninja from another dimension. The challenge comes in a tradition unfamiliar to Leonardo, but worrisome familiar to Master Splinter.<ref>[http://www.ninjaturtles.com/cartoon/2003/synopses/35.html The Ultimate Ninja] Ninja Turtles Official Website. February 19, 2008</ref>\n*Villain: The Ultimate Ninja\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=37\n |EpisodeNumber2=11\n |Title=The Return of Nano\n |DirectedBy=Chuck Patton\n |WrittenBy=Eric Luke\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2004|2|21}}\n |ProdCode=S02E11\n |ShortSummary=Nano, the [[nanorobotics|nanorobot]] who met his supposed [[Nano (TMNT 2003 Episode)|demise]] in the junyard, reawakens and reassembles. With a newfound motivation to create a [[nuclear family|family]], Nano breaks his \"father,\" [[Harry Parker (TMNT)|Harry Parker]], out of [[Rikers Island]] prison and kidnaps his \"mother\", [[Dr. Richards]], from her laboratory. When his \"family\" doesn't turn out as he hoped, Nano begins to wreak havoc on [[Coney Island]], where April and Casey happen to be on a \"not-a-[[courtship|date]].\"\n\n* Villain: Nano\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=38\n |EpisodeNumber2=12\n |Title=What a Croc!\n |DirectedBy=Chuck Patton\n |WrittenBy=[[Ben Townsend]]\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2004|2|28}}\n |ProdCode=S02E12\n |ShortSummary=Michelangelo helps Donatello by exploring the underwater access way beneath the lair. Here he encounters [[Leatherhead (TMNT)|Leatherhead]], a mutant [[crocodile]] torn between two personalities: a peaceful inventor and a vicious animal. The Turtles go with Leatherhead to his sewer home and encounter an old foe with whom Leatherhead has teamed up.\n\n* Villain: Baxter Stockman\n* Based on Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles, Volume One Issue #45, \"Leatherhead Too\".\n\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=39\n |EpisodeNumber2=13\n |Title=Return to the Underground\n |DirectedBy=Chuck Patton\n |WrittenBy=Marty Isenberg\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2004|3|6}}\n |ProdCode=S02E13\n |ShortSummary=Determined to find a cure for his [[Notes from the Underground (TMNT 2003 Episode)|genetically mutated friends]], Donatello and his brothers return to the subterranean city. Unfortunately, when the Turtles return, they find that their friends have reverted to monsters and the Crystal Moon is nowhere to be seen.\n\nVillains: The Underground Mutants\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=40\n |EpisodeNumber2=14\n |Title=City at War, Part 1\n |DirectedBy=Chuck Patton\n |WrittenBy=Eric Luke\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2004|3|13}}\n |ProdCode=S02E14\n |ShortSummary=With the Shredder gone, the Foot Clan, the Purple Dragons, and the [[Mafia|mob]] struggle to control New York City, quickly turning the streets into a dangerous [[wikt:turf war|turf war]]. Feeling the onus of the chaos in the streets, Leonardo sets out to quell the situation while Raphael argues that it's not their fight.\n\n* Villains: The Mob, the Foot and the Purple Dragons\n* Based on Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles, Volume One \"City at War:\".\n\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=41\n |EpisodeNumber2=15\n |Title=City at War, Part 2\n |DirectedBy=Chuck Patton\n |WrittenBy=Marty Isenberg\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2004|3|20}}\n |ProdCode=S02E15\n |ShortSummary=The Turtles become embroiled in the turf war as they face off against the Foot, headed by the Elite Guard, while a mob-funded attack robot created by Baxter Stockman and the Purple Dragons, led by Hun, besiege the Foot's rundown headquarters. To make matters more complicated, a ninja from Japan named [[Karai (character)|Karai]] enters the fray, though her intentions are ambiguous. At her mercy, the Turtles have no choice but to bargain with her.\n\n*Villains: the Foot, The Purple Dragons and the Mob\n* Based on Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles, Volume One \"City at War:\".\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=42\n |EpisodeNumber2=16\n |Title=City at War, Part 3\n |DirectedBy=Chuck Patton\